  "local_port": 54584,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My driving license is lost. How do I apply for a new one?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear about your lost driving license. The process for applying for a new driving license after losing your original one can vary depending on where you live, but generally, these steps will help guide you through the process:\n\n1. **Notify the Authorities:**\n   - **Report the Loss:** If required in your area, report the loss to your local police department. They may provide a report that can be helpful when applying for a replacement.\n\n2. **Check Requirements:**\n   - **Department of Motor Vehicles (DMV):** Visit the website of your local DMV (or equivalent agency) to check the specific requirements for applying for a replacement driving license in your state or country.\n\n3. **Gather Necessary Documents:**\n   - **Identification:** You will need to provide some form of identification. This can include your passport, birth certificate, or other government-issued ID.\n   - **Proof of Residency:** Provide documents that prove your current address, such as utility bills, bank statements, or rental agreements.\n   - **Social Security Number:** In some places, you may be required to provide your Social Security Number or equivalent.\n\n4. **Fill Out Application Form:**\n   - **Replacement License Application:** Obtain and complete the application form for a replacement license. Forms are usually available online or at the DMV office.\n\n5. **Visit the DMV:**\n   - **In-Person Visit:** You might need to visit the DMV in person to submit your application, pay any required fees, and have your photo taken. Some jurisdictions may allow online applications.\n\n6. **Pay Fees:**\n   - **Replacement Fee:** Be prepared to pay a fee for the replacement license. Fees vary depending on your location.\n\n7. **Wait for New License:**\n   - **Processing Time:** After you\u2019ve submitted your application, you might receive a temporary license while you wait for your new one to be mailed to you. Processing times can vary.\n\n8. **Keep Records:**\n   - **Keep Copies:** It\u2019s a good idea to keep copies of all documents related to your application and the records of your lost license.\n\nFeel free to provide your location for more specific guidance.",
